geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: The GNSS antenna is mounted on top of a 0.10 m high stainless steel spacer attached to a brass plate with a forced centered stainless steel bolt embedded on top of a 1.5 m high concrete pier, 0.40 m in diameter. The concrete pier is anchored to exposed bedrock. Horizon is clear of obstructions.

geo:siteLocation.geo:notes: CHUR is a continuously tracking GNSS station and is part of the Canadian Active Control System (CACS). The station is located at the Geological Survey of Canada regional seismic station in Churchill, Manitoba. The station is collocated with the GNSS station CHU2.
